CMD ["echo", "-e", "The JaCoCo agent collects execution information and dumps it on request or 
when the JVM exits. There are three different modes for execution data output:

 1. File System: At JVM termination execution data is written to a local 
 file.
 2. TCP Socket Server: External tools can connect to the JVM and retrieve 
 execution data over the socket connection. Optional execution data reset 
 and execution data dump on VM exit is possible.
 3. TCP Socket Client: At startup the JaCoCo agent connects to a given TCP 
 endpoint. Execution data is written to the socket connection on request. 
 Optional execution data reset and execution data dump on VM exit is possible.

The agent jacocoagent.jar is part of the JaCoCo distribution and includes all 
required dependencies. A Java agent can be activated with the following JVM option:

 -javaagent:/jacoco/lib/jacocoagent.jar=[option1]=[value1],[option2]=[value2]

More info please visit: https://www.eclemma.org/jacoco/trunk/doc/agent.html
"]
